info.headline: High Wind Warning issued October 28 at 9:14PM PDT until October 30 at 10:00PM PDT by NWS Oxnard
info.description: ...WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 11 PM PDT THIS EVENING... ...HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 PM PDT MONDAY... * WHAT...For the Wind Advisory, northwest to north winds 20 to 30 mph with gusts to 45 mph are expected. For the High Wind Warning, northeast winds 25 to 40 mph with gusts to 60 mph are expected. * WHERE...Interstate 5 Corridor. * WHEN...For the Wind Advisory, until 11 PM PDT this evening. For the High Wind Warning, from 11 PM this evening to 10 PM PDT Monday. * IMPACTS...Damaging winds will blow down large objects such as trees and power lines. Power outages are expected. Travel will be difficult, especially for drivers of high profile vehicles.
info.instruction: People should avoid being outside in forested areas and around large trees. If possible, remain indoors and avoid windows. Use extra caution if you must drive
